---
// src/pages/projects/polarity-gps.astro
import Project from '../../layouts/Project.astro';
---
<Project
  title="Polarity GPS"
  description="Polarity GPS is a platform designed to surface what exists in your neighborhood but does not appear in recommendation."
  evidenceState="platform-live-study-pending"
  evidenceLabel="Platform live, formal study pending"
>

  <section class="act">
    <p class="act-body">Discovery platforms surface what is around you.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="act">
    <p class="act-body">
      They surface what is popular around you. Popularity is not the same as presence.
      What exists at the neighborhood scale (the store that has been there for twenty years,
      the church that anchors the block) is not what recommendation surfaces,
      because it does not optimize for engagement. That gap is what GPS is being built to measure.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>The question</h2>
    <p>
      Is the gap between what recommendation surfaces and what actually exists in a
      neighborhood measurable? The platform is live at <a href="https://polaritygps.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">polaritygps.com</a>.
      Community partnerships are established with MUSEOFRI and GOODhumanz in Providence.
      The formal measurement study is the next step.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Evidence</h2>
    <div class="evidence-block">
      <p>
        Platform live. Community partnerships established.
        Formal scored study not yet run. That is what comes next.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

</Project>

<style>
  @import '../../styles/project.css';
</style>
